Vendored real-page snapshot — NOTICE and provenance
===================================================

Why this directory exists
-------------------------
Referent extraction has to be written for real pages. Every other page in
`clearway/fixtures/` is synthetic and tiny — the vendored ACT cases have rendered
bodies of 2 to 220 characters — so an extractor that simply returned the whole
document body would score perfectly against them and be useless on a production
page. Fitting extraction to the fixtures would relocate this project's own
overfitting lesson into the input pipeline.

So the extractors are reviewed against a snapshot of a named, real page, and the
extracted output is committed next to it. That makes the review auditable: a
reader can see exactly what each extractor produced on a 170,000-character
document, rather than being asked to trust that someone checked.

