Why this page is representative
-------------------------------
It is a real, hand-authored production page — not a generated test case — and it
exercises every extractor in this module at once:

  * 170,720 characters of DOM and 10,107 characters of *rendered* body text
    (roughly 46x the largest ACT fixture body), so budgets and truncation are
    genuinely tested rather than never reached;
  * a `<title>`, an `<h1>`, a `<main>` landmark and a `<meta name="description">`
    — all four page-topic tiers exist on one page, so tier precedence is
    observable instead of theoretical;
  * 20 headings, so "nearest preceding heading" has to actually choose;
  * 162 links in prose, lists and tables — the in-context link case;
  * a labelled search field — the accessible-name case;
  * deep, real nesting, so the ancestor-depth cap and the context window are
    exercised on structures nobody wrote for a test.

It is also in this project's own subject domain and on a site whose material this
repository already vendors under the same licence (see `../act-gold/NOTICE`).

